NAME
    gcloud alpha privateca roots - manage root certificate authorities

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha privateca roots COMMAND [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Manage root certificate authorities.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

COMMANDS
    COMMAND is one of the following:

     add-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Add IAM policy binding for a root Certificate Authority.

     create
        (ALPHA) Create a new root certificate authority.

     delete
        (ALPHA) Permanently delete a root certificate authority.

     describe
        (ALPHA) Get metadata for a root Certificate Authority.

     disable
        (ALPHA) Disable a root certificate authority.

     enable
        (ALPHA) Enable a root certificate authority.

     get-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Get the IAM policy for a root certificate authority.

     list
        (ALPHA) List the root certificate authorities within a location.

     remove-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Remove IAM policy binding for a root Certificate Authority.

     set-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Set the IAM policy for a root Certificate Authority.

     update
        (ALPHA) Update an existing root certificate authority.

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. If this command fails with API permission errors despite
    specifying the right project, you may be trying to access an API with an
    invitation-only early access whitelist.

